Preheat oven to 200°F. Generously grease two baking sheets with butter. Place in oven, then turn off oven, keeping baking sheets warm. In a large heavy saucepan combine sugar, corn syrup, water, and salt. Bring mixture to boiling; add butter. Clip a candy thermometer to side of pan. Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches 250°F. Stir in cashews. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 305°F. Remove pan from heat; remove thermometer. Quickly stir in baking soda and vanilla. Stir in coconut. Spread mixture in a thin layer on each warm baking sheet. Cool. Break into bite-size pieces.